IT seems that soon it will not only be seen in sci-fi movies, flying are becoming reality. A Dutch engineering company named PAL-V International B.V. says a full production flying vehicle will be available from next year. "you start at a point where you don't want to start and you end up in a place where you don't want to be," PAL-V International chief Robert Dingemanse told AFP. "The Pal-V is the perfect product for city-to-city mobility," he said. According to the company the flying car will be used to fly when one is outside cities, and whiles in the city the owners will the drive the cars. Dingemanse pointed out that car, will have two seats, retractable helicopter blades and will be powered by a petrol engine.